Sentencas: For better performance and enhanced stability, the traditional MIEC cathode material BSCF was optimized by niobium-doping for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) with an electron-blocking layer.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8-xFe0.2NbxO3-δ (x≤ 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with an electron-blocking interlayer

Sentencas: The cathode materials Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8-xFe0.2NbxO3-delta (x <= 0.1) (BSCFNbx) were synthesized and the effects of niobium-doping level was investigated systematically.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8-xFe0.2NbxO3-δ (x≤ 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with an electron-blocking interlayer

Sentencas: Our experimental results revealed that as the niobium-doping level increases, the resistibility of BSCFNbx to CO2 and H2O is enhanced greatly, the thermal expansion coefficient of BSCFNbx (x <= 0.1) decreases from 21.74 x 10(-6) K-1 to 18.74 x 10(-6) K-1, indicating that niobium-doping is conducive to chemical stability and combination between cathode and electrolyte.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8-xFe0.2NbxO3-δ (x≤ 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with an electron-blocking interlayer

Sentencas: By mean of XPS characterization, the ratio of adsorption oxygen to lattice oxygen in BSCFNb0.(05) reached the highest value among this series, which means the highest oxygen transport rate.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8-xFe0.2NbxO3-δ (x≤ 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with an electron-blocking interlayer

Sentencas: In NiO-BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta vertical bar Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (NiO-BZCY vertical bar SDC) - based single-cell applications, the highest electrochemical performance of 882 mW cm(-2) and the lowest polarization resistance of 0.14 Omega cm(2 )at 700 degrees C occurred when the xis 0.05 in BSCFNbx.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8-xFe0.2NbxO3-δ (x≤ 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with an electron-blocking interlayer

Sentencas: The electron-blocking layer generated in sintering process of the NiO-BZCY vertical bar SDC half-cell promotes the open circuit voltage (OCV) over 1.0 V, ensuring high performance of single-cells in our investigation.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8-xFe0.2NbxO3-δ (x≤ 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with an electron-blocking interlayer

Sentencas: This work indicates that niobium-doping is an effective strategy to promote simultaneously performance and stability of cathode material for IT-SOFCs, and BSCFNb0.05 is a good potential material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8-xFe0.2NbxO3-δ (x≤ 0.1) as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with an electron-blocking interlayer
